<div class="blog-split--image-mask">
<img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.rogerebert.com/uploads/blog_post/primary_image/interviews/wagner-moura-civil-war-interview/primary_Civil_War_Screengrab_005.jpg" />
</div>
</figure>
<figcaption class="blog-split--info column">
<a class="blog-split--category" href="/interviews"><h5>Interviews</h5>
</a><a class="blog-split--title" href="/interviews/wagner-moura-civil-war-interview"><h3>Wagner Moura Is Still Holding On To Hope</h3>
</a><div class="blog-split--byline">
<span class="byline">
<a href="/contributors/tim-grierson">Tim Grierson</a>
</span>
<time class="time">April 11, 2024</time>

</div>
<p class="blog-split--excerpt">
The Civil War star explains how his early career as a journalist informs his performance in Alex Garland’s dystopian thriller—and why he’s not nearly as pessimistic about the future as his character is.

</p>
</figcaption>
</div>
</article>
</section>

<section class="page-content--block">
<article class="blog-split">
<div class="columns">
<figure class="blog-split--image column is-7">
<div class="blog-split--image-mask">
<img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.rogerebert.com/uploads/blog_post/primary_image/interviews/zellner-interview/primary_Sasquatch_Still_8.jpg" />
</div>
</figure>
<figcaption class="blog-split--info column">
<a class="blog-split--category" href="/interviews"><h5>Interviews</h5>
</a><a class="blog-split--title" href="/interviews/zellner-interview"><h3>The Zellner Brothers Take a Walk in the Woods with Sasquatch Sunset</h3>
</a><div class="blog-split--byline">
<span class="byline">
<a href="/contributors/robert-daniels">Robert Daniels</a>
</span>
<time class="time">April 09, 2024</time>

</div>
<p class="blog-split--excerpt">
David and Nathan Zellner have always made movies about outsiders, but their latest goes to new extremes. They sat down with Robert Daniels in Berlin to talk about Sasquatch Sunset, one of the most unusual and unexpectedly moving films you'll&hellip;

</p>
</figcaption>
</div>
</article>
</section>

<section class="page-content--block">
<article class="blog-split">
<div class="columns">
<figure class="blog-split--image column is-7">
<div class="blog-split--image-mask">
<img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.rogerebert.com/uploads/blog_post/primary_image/interviews/alice-rohrwacher-interview/primary_LA_CHIMERA3._Courtesy_of_NEON.jpg" />
</div>
</figure>
<figcaption class="blog-split--info column">
<a class="blog-split--category" href="/interviews"><h5>Interviews</h5>
</a><a class="blog-split--title" href="/interviews/alice-rohrwacher-interview"><h3>Female Filmmakers in Focus: Alice Rohrwacher on La Chimera</h3>
</a><div class="blog-split--byline">
<span class="byline">
<a href="/contributors/marya-e-gates">Marya E. Gates</a>
</span>
<time class="time">April 03, 2024</time>

</div>
<p class="blog-split--excerpt">
An interview with the director of the acclaimed new film starring Josh O'Connor.

</p>
</figcaption>
</div>
</article>
</section>

